Create a method in Java that takes two integers as parameters and returns their sum. Call the method with some values and print the result.

import java.util.Scanner;
public class Main{
    public static void main(String args[]){
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        int a= sc.nextInt();
        int b = sc.nextInt();
        System.out.println(sum(a,b));
    }
    static int sum(int x,int y){
        return x+y;
    }
}
